      "writtenOn": "2026-05-15T08:45:05Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "1. No. There is such thing as Public Domain code.\n\n2. It does, as only adult humans and corporations can hold copyright. I guess human children can inherit \"ownership\" of a copyright, but they need adults to \"do\" anything with that copyright, such as attaching licenses or suing copyright violators. Also, the human must have enough \"creative expression\" in the text form (not just ideas behind it). A work without copyright owner meeting such requirements is Public Domain by default, if there are no other conditions making it some other form of intellectual ownership (patents, trademarks, classified information, ...).\n\nI guess this document could give a better summary of differences between contributor, author and copyright holder.",
